title: Dartmouth scores 20 straight; beats CCSU 34-7
text:
Williams throws for 3 TDs, Stone runs for 2 to lead Dartmouth over CCSU 34-7 THE ASSOCIATED PRESS  15   3:15   
Subjects: 
Connecticut (333) 

NEW BRITAIN, Connecticut — Dalyn Williams threw three touchdown passes, Ryder Stone ran for two scores and Dartmouth beat Central Connecticut 34-7 on Saturday for its eighth straight victory. 
Dartmouth scored 20 straight points in the second half. 
Williams was 23 of 33 for 249 yards and one interception for Dartmouth (5-0), with TD passes of 44-yards to Jon Marc Carrier to open the scoring and 8 and 3 yards to Cameron Skaff. Victor Williams had seven catches for 95 yards. Stone gained 49 yards on 13 carries with two short TD runs. 
Jacob Dolegala and Tavion Pauldo combined for 172 yards passing and two interceptions for CCSU (2-5). 
CCSU scored in the second quarter when Chris Tinkham forced Kyle Bramble to fumble on the Dartmouth 1 and Cameron Nash recovered it in the end zone. The Blue Devils were outgained 443 yards to 225 and were held to just 53 yards rushing.
